              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USATAM"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed using",
                "superconducting cyclotron and a mass separator MARS",
                "at the Cyclotron Institute."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Methane (CH4) gas in the scattering chamber was used",
                "as safe substitute for hydrogen sample. Gas pressure",
                "was changed for different experimental runs between",
                "930 mbar (low pressure) and 1040 mbar (high pressure)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Plastic BC-400 scintillator foil at the",
                "entrance of scattering chamber was used to monitor the",
                "beam, identify the contaminant 10C ions and to start",
                "the time-of-flight system."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Ionization chamber at the entrance of",
                "scattering chamber was used for additional",
                "identification of 13-O ions."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "IOCH",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Telescope consisting of windowless",
                "ionization chamber and a pair of quadrant Si",
                "telescopes, each consisting of four Si detectors",
                "with dimensions of 12.5 x 12.5 x 1 mm3 followed by a",
                "scintillation veto detector was used for reaction",
                "product identification."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " E-dE method and time of flight was used",
                "for reaction product identification. Excitation",
                "function was measured by thick target inverse",
                "kinematics method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Beam of 13-O ions was produced via 14N(p,2n)13-O",
                "reaction. 14N ions accelerated in superconducting",
                "cyclotron to energy of 38 MeV/A bombarded cooled",
                "hydrogen gas target with pressure of 3 atm. After",
                "separation in mass separator MARS the resulting 13-O",
                "beam had energy of 31 MeV/A and intensity of 5.0E+3",
                "ions/sec. There was 15% contamination of 10C in",
                "13-O beam. The energy of 13-O ions was degraded using",
                "polypropylene foils with total thickness of 1.5mm to",
                "approx. 10 MeV/A."
              ]
            }
          ],
